{
  "stem": "22889.1",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My home in Nowy-Targ-- Nowy-Targ was a small town.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It had no industries, merely several workshop.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But there were many Jewish artisans and craftsmen of considerable skill and enterprise.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The main synagogue in our town was built in modern style.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "It accommodate 800 worshipers.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "The first cantor for the main synagogue was the very famous Yossele Rosenblatt.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] After a while, he was engaged as the chief cantor in the Hamburg temple in Germany, and later went to the United States, where he became worldwide known.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Nowy-Targ also had several other synagogues, some of Hasidic centers of learning, which added greatly to the Hasidic atmosphere in town.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "The Jewish cemetery in Nowy-Targ was outside the town, at one time.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "It abounded with headstone for the graves-- of the graves of the great rabbis and community leaders, as well as simple folks.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "During the Holocaust, the cemetery witnessed a tragic end of Nowy-Targ Jewery.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "In August 30, 1942, following the last round up, the town there remains several hundred Jews. 500 of them were taken there, and tortured, and shot.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Among them was my father.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Their bodies were thrown into the common grave.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Today, this cemetery is neglected, forgotten, markers of the past.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "The Jewish population in Nowy-Targ were 3,000, before the war. 39 of us remain alive today, after the war.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "We had, also, one of the largest Zionist movement organizations in the country.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "To name a few, Akiva, Mizrahi, [NON-ENGLISH], Betar.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "We also-- we also were very active in sports competition against our Polish friends and enemies.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "I remember very well, when I was growing up, the year 1938, anti-Semitism in our town became very strong and active.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "Polish anti-Semitism became organized-- the Endeks, we used to call them, the Endeks.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
